{"parse":{"title":"strawberry","pageid":4841,"redirects":[],"wikitext":"{{also|Strawberry}}\n==English==\n[[Image:Strawberries in white bowl.jpg|thumb|Strawberries in a bowl]]\n[[Image:Wild strawberries on straw.jpg|thumb|Wild strawberries strung on a stalk of grass]]\n\n===Etymology===\n{{etymon|en|id=red fruit|:inh|enm:strawberie<id:strawberry>|tree=1}}\nFrom {{inh|en|enm|strawberie}}, {{m|enm|strawbery}}, from {{inh|en|ang|strēawberġe}}, corresponding to {{compound|en|straw|berry}}.\n\nOf various theories advanced to explain the name, the two most plausible are:<ref>{{cite-journal|last1=Fridell|first1=Staffan|last2=Svanberg|first2=Ingvar|year=2024|title=On the etymology of ''strawberry''|journal=Studia Neophilologica|volume=96|issue=2|pages=303–310|url=https://www.tandfonline.com/doi/full/10.1080/00393274.2024.2329185}}</ref> \n# from the fact that wild strawberries grow on straw-like runners (compare {{cog|no|stråbær}}, denoting cranberries, which grow in a similar way);\n# from the practice, still common in parts of Europe, of gathering strawberries by stringing them on a straw or stalk.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|en|/ˈstɹɔːb(ə)ɹi/|[ʃt͡ʃɹɔːbɹi]|a=UK}}\n** {{audio|en|LL-Q1860 (eng)-Xavier hillier-strawberry.wav|a=UK,/str/-retraction}}\n* {{IPA|en|/ˈstɹɔˌbɛɹi/|a=GA,non-cot-caught}}\n** {{IPA|en|/ˈstɹɑˌbɛɹi/|/ˈstɹɒˌbɛɹi/|a=cot-caught}}\n*** {{audio|en|En-us-strawberry.ogg|a=California}}\n* {{hyph|en|straw|ber|ry}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{en-noun|~}}\n\n# {{senseid|en|Q14458220}}The sweet, usually [[red]], edible [[accessory fruit]] of certain plants of the genus {{taxfmt|Fragaria|genus}}.\n#: {{ux|en|They went to pick '''strawberries''' today.}}\n#* {{quote-journal|en|author=Jessie Yeung|title=Pope Francis loves nouns but is ‘allergic’ to adjectives|magazine=w:CNN|url=https://www.theguardian.com/sport/blog/2011/sep/01/sport-language-harry-pearson|date=2019-09-24|passage=Communication is a kind of beauty, he said – and “beauty manifests itself from the noun itself, without '''strawberries''' on the cake.”|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190927032029/https://www.cnn.com/2019/09/24/us/pope-adjectives-intl-hnk-scli/|quotee=w:Pope Francis}}\n#* {{quote-journal|en|author=Casey Barber|title=Strawberry season has arrived. Here are tips for enjoying spring’s sweetest treat|magazine=w:CNN|url=https://www.cnn.com/2022/05/09/health/strawberries-may-recipe-wellness|date=2022-05-09|passage=Is there a sweeter time of year than '''strawberry''' season? As soon as the trees start bursting into pink buds, the first '''strawberries''' can’t be far behind at the farmers market.|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20220704104400/https://www.cnn.com/2022/05/09/health/strawberries-may-recipe-wellness/}}\n# Any plant of the genus {{taxfmt|Fragaria|genus}} (that bears such fruit).\n#: {{ux|en|She has the best '''strawberry''' patch I've ever seen.}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=1886|translator=H.L. Br&aelig;kstad|author=w:Peter Christen Asbj&oslash;rnsen| title=Folk and Fairy Tales| page=170|passage=He told his father, and said it would be just suitable work for him to run about fields and woods amongst the '''strawberry''' hills after a flock of hares, and now and then lie down and take a nap on some sunny hill.}}\n# The [[berry]] of the [[strawberry tree]] ({{taxfmt|Arbutus|genus}})\n# A dark [[pinkish]] [[red]] [[color]], like that of the fruit; [[strawberry red]].\n#: {{color panel|B64140}}\n# {{lb|en|rare}} Something resembling a strawberry, especially a reddish bruise, [[birthmark]], or infantile [[hemangioma]] ([[naevus]]).\n#: {{coi|en|[[strawberry mark|'''strawberry''' marks]]}}\n#* {{quote-journal|en-GB|author=Fiona Vera-Gray|quotee=Almina|title=‘Everything is hairless’: what 100 women taught me about porn and body confidence|work=The Guardian|date=2024-02-20|url=https://www.theguardian.com/society/2024/feb/20/everything-is-hairless-what-100-women-taught-me-about-porn-and-body-confidence|issn=0261-3077|passage=I have stretch marks and '''strawberry''' legs [follicles or blocked pores that appear as black dots]{{sic}}; discoloration all over my body.}}\n# {{lb|en|US|slang}} A [[prostitute]] who exchanges sexual services for [[crack cocaine]].\n#* {{quote-song|en|title=Dope Man|artist=w:N.W.A|year=1987|album=w:N.W.A. and the Posse|passage=Come home and see her mouth on the dopeman's dick / '''Strawberry''', just look and you'll see her}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=1992|author=Kathleen Boyle|title=Homeless crack cocaine abusers|page=40| passage={{...}} infamous in Los Angeles through media reports: the crack houses and \"'''strawberries'''\" (women who exchange sex for crack) {{...}}}}\n#* {{quote-song|en|year=1995|author={{w|B.G. Knocc Out}} & {{w|Dresta}}|title=Compton Hoe|url=https://genius.com/Bg-knocc-out-and-dresta-compton-hoe-lyrics|album={{w|Real Brothas}}|text=I'm makin mo' deals than a '''strawberry''' might<br />I'll lick your clit, if you suck my pipe}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=1997|author=Peter Collier; David Horowitz|title=The Race Card|page=91| passage=The desperate addiction associated with the drug has made \"'''strawberries'''\" — prostitutes who work for crack — fixtures of the {{...}}}}\n# A [[butt plug]] with one end shaped like a strawberry fruit.\n#* {{quote-journal|en|author=Alessandra Schade|quotee=Stella Barey|title=‘We’re sick of the OnlyFans model’: Stella Barey’s porn site lets gen Z sex workers have a life|journal=The Guardian|date=2025-11-07|url=https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/ng-interactive/2025/nov/07/stella-barey-hidden-porn-creators-onlyfans|passage=When Barey decided in 2020 to pursue porn full-time, she did not imagine that at 28 she would spend more time hunched over a desk – not in the fun way – making flow charts, scheduling Zoom calls, and sending pitch decks. “I’m at my happiest when I’m making a video like putting a '''strawberry''' in my butt and pushing it out,” she says. “Now I’m on calls all day and I have tech neck.”}}\n\n====Synonyms====\n* {{alt|en|earthberry||rare}}\n* {{alt|en|strawb||informal|rare}}\n\n====Hypernyms====\n* {{l|en|fruit}}\n** {{l|en|berry}}\n\n====Meronyms====\n* {{sense|fruit}} {{l|en|anthocyanin}}\n\n====Derived terms====\n{{col|en|pineberry|strasberry|strawbana|strawberryless\n|{{vern|alpine strawberry}} ({{taxfmt|Fragaria vesca|species}})\n|[[barren strawberry]] ({{taxlink|Potentilla sterilis|species}} or {{taxlink|Waldsteinia fragarioides|species}})\n|[[beach strawberry]] ({{taxlink|Fragaria chiloensis|species}})\n|{{vern|bog strawberry}} ({{vern|marsh cinquefoil}}, {{taxlink|Comarum palustre|species}})\n|[[Chilean strawberry]] ({{taxlink|Fragaria chiloensis|species}})\n|[[Chinese strawberry tree]] ({{taxfmt|Myrica rubra|species}})\n|[[coastal strawberry]] ({{taxlink|Fragaria chiloensis|species}})\n|{{vern|creeping strawberry pine}} ({{taxlink|Microcachrys tetragona|species}})\n|crushed strawberry|strawberry clover\n|[[false strawberry]] (''{{taxfmt|Duchesnea indica|species}}/{{taxfmt|Potentilla indica|species}}'')\n|{{vern|garden strawberry}} ({{taxlink|Fragaria × ananassa|nothospecies}})\n|{{vern|hautbois strawberry}}, {{vern|hautboy strawberry}} ({{taxlink|Fragaria moschata|species}})\n|[[Indian strawberry]] (''{{taxfmt|Duchesnea indica|species}}/{{taxfmt|Potentilla indica|species}}'')\n|{{vern|Irish strawberry}} ({{taxfmt|Arbutus unedo|species}})\n|[[mock strawberry]] (''{{taxfmt|Duchesnea indica|species}}/{{taxfmt|Potentilla indica|species}}'')\n|{{vern|musk strawberry}} ({{taxlink|Fragaria moschata|species}})\n|red strawberry tongue|strawberry bud weevil|strawberry weevil\n|{{vern|scarlet strawberry}} ({{taxlink|Fragaria virginiana|species}})\n|[[sea strawberry]] ({{taxlink|Gersemia rubiformis|species}}; {{taxlink|Aplidium elegans|species}})\n|strawberrita\n|strawberryade\n|strawberry aldehyde\n|strawberry aphid|strawberry wine\n|[[strawberry begonia]] ({{taxfmt|Saxifraga stolonifera|species}})\n|{{vern|strawberry blite}} ({{taxlink|Blitum capitatum|species}})\n|strawberry blond,strawberry blonde \n|{{l|en|strawberry bush}} ({{taxlink|Euonymus americanus|species}})\n|strawberry cactus\n|[[strawberry crab]] ({{taxlink|Neoliomera pubescens|species}})\n|strawberry gallbladder\n|strawberry generation\n|[[strawberry geranium]] ({{taxfmt|Saxifraga stolonifera|species}})\n|strawberry guava\n|strawberry hemangioma\n|Strawberry Hill\n|strawberry leaf|strawberry legs\n|strawberry mark\n|strawberry moon\n|[[strawberry myrtle]] ({{taxlink|Ugni molinae|species}})\n|[[strawberry pear]] ({{taxfmt|Stenocereus|genus}} (syn. {{taxfmt|Hylocereus|genus}}) spp.)\n|strawberry raspberry\n|strawberry roan\n|strawberry root weevil\n|[[strawberry saxifrage]] ({{taxfmt|Saxifraga stolonifera|species}})\n|strawberry shortcake\n|{{vern|strawberry shrub}} ({{taxfmt|Calycanthaceae|family}} spp.)\n|[[strawberry snail]] ({{taxlink|Trochulus striolatus|species}}\n|strawberrytini\n|{{l|en|strawberry tomato}} (''[[Physalis]]'' spp.)\n|strawberry tongue\n|strawberry tree\n|{{vern|Virginia strawberry}} ({{taxlink|Fragaria virginiana|species}})\n|{{l|en|wild strawberry}} ({{taxfmt|Fragaria vesca|species}})\n|[[wood strawberry]], [[woodland strawberry]] ({{taxfmt|Fragaria vesca|species}})\n|{{vern|yellow strawberry}} (''{{taxfmt|Duchesnea indica|species}}/{{taxfmt|Potentilla indica|species}}'')\n}}\n\n====Descendants====\n{{top2}}\n* {{desc|bn|স্ট্রবেরি|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|my|စတော်ဘယ်ရီ|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|yue|士多啤梨|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|ny|sitiroberi|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|gu|સ્ટ્રોબેરી|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|hi|स्ट्रॉबेरी|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|id|stroberi|lbor=1}}\n* {{desc|kn|ಸ್ಟ್ರಾಬೆರಿ|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|csb|stroberi|qq=Canada, United States|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|lo|ໝາກສະຕໍເບີຣີ|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|ms|strawberi|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|th|สตรอว์เบอร์รี|bor=1}}\n{{bottom}}\n\n====Translations====\n{{trans-top|accessory fruit}}\n* Abenaki: {{t|abe|mskikoimins}}\n* Abkhaz: {{t|ab|аҵыҵындра}}\n* Afrikaans: {{t+|af|aarbei}}\n* Ainu: {{t|ain|エマゥリ|tr=emawri}}\n* Albanian: {{t+|sq|dredhëz|f}}, {{t+|sq|luleshtrydhe|m}}, {{t|sq|manë toke|f}}\n* Aleut: {{t|ale|tuzaangas|p}}\n* Altai:\n*: Southern Altai: {{t|alt|јер јилек}}, {{t|alt|кой-јиилек}}\n* Amharic: {{t|am|እንጆሪ}}\n* Arabic: {{t|ar|فَرَاوْلَة|f}}, {{t|ar|فِرِيز|m}}, {{t|ar|تُوت اَلْأَرْض|m}}\n*: Egyptian Arabic: {{t|arz|فراولة|tr=farawla}}\n*: Hijazi Arabic: {{t|acw|فراولة|f|tr=farāwla}}\n*: Iraqi Arabic: {{t|acm|شليك|m|tr=šillēk}}, {{t|ary|چلكة|tr=čilka}}\n*: Moroccan Arabic: {{t|ary|توت الأرض|tr=tūt el-ʔarḍ}}, {{t|ary|فريز|m|tr=frīz}}\n*: South Levantine Arabic: {{t|ajp|فراولة|tr=farāwla}}, {{t|ajp|توت الأرض|tr=tūt il-ʔarḍ}}\n* Aramaic:\n*: Assyrian Neo-Aramaic: {{t|aii|ܦ̮ܪܵܒ݂ܠܵܐ|tr=frawla|m}}, {{t|aii|ܟ̰ܸܠܲܝܩܵܐ|tr=čillayqa|m}}\n* Armenian: {{t+|hy|ելակ}}, {{t+|hy|մորի}} {{q|wild}}\n* Aromanian: {{t|rup|cãpsheanã|f}}\n* Asturian: {{t+|ast|fresa|f}}\n* Azerbaijani: {{t|az|çiyələyi}}, {{t+|az|çiyələk}}\n* Basque: {{t|eu|marrubi}}\n* Belarusian: {{t|be|суні́ца|f}} {{q|wild}}, {{t|be|клубні́ца|f}} {{q|cultivated}}; {{t|be|труска́ўка|f}}\n* Bengali: {{t|bn|স্ট্রবেরি}}\n* Breton: {{t+|br|sivi}}, {{t+|br|sivienn}}\n* Bulgarian: {{t+|bg|я́года|f}}\n* Burmese: {{t+|my|စတော်ဘယ်ရီ}}\n* Buryat: {{t|bua|гүлзөөргэнэ}}, {{t|bua|зэдэгэнэ}}\n* Caijia: {{t|sit-cai|tɔ²⁴mɔ²¹}}\n* Catalan: {{t+|ca|maduixa|f}}, {{t+|ca|fraula|f}}\n* Cherokee: {{t|chr|ᎠᏅ}}\n* Chichewa: {{t|ny|sitiroberi}}\n* Chinese:\n*: Cantonese: {{t+|yue|士多啤梨|tr=si6 do1 be1 lei2}}, {{t|yue|草莓|tr=cou2 mui4-2; cou2 mui4}}\n*: Hakka: {{t|hak|草莓|tr=chhó-mòi}}\n*: Hokkien: {{t+|nan-hbl|草莓|tr=chháu-m̂}}, {{t|nan-hbl|莓仔|tr=m̂-á}}, {{t|nan-hbl|虎莓|tr=hó͘-m̂}}\n*: Mandarin: {{t+|cmn|草莓}}\n* Chinook Jargon: {{t|chn|amuti}}\n* Cornish: {{t|kw|sevien|f}}\n* Cree: {{t|cr|ᐅᑌᐦᐃᒥᐣ}}, {{t|cr|ᒥᑌᐦᐃᒥᐣ|cinanimate}}\n*: Atikamekw: {{t|atj|otehiminan}}\n* Crimean Tatar: {{t|crh|джилек}}\n* Czech: {{t+|cs|jahoda|f}}\n* Danish: {{t+|da|jordbær|n}}\n* Dutch: {{t+|nl|aardbei|f}}\n* Elfdalian: {{t|ovd|juordgubb|m}}\n* Esperanto: {{t+|eo|frago}}\n* Estonian: {{t+|et|maasikas}}, {{t|et|maasikmari}}\n* Faroese: {{t|fo|jarðber|n}}\n* Finnish: {{t+|fi|mansikka}}\n* Fox: {{t|sac|têhimini}}\n* French: {{t+|fr|fraise|f}}\n* Frisian:\n*: West Frisian: {{t|fy|ierdbei|c}}\n* Friulian: {{t|fur|freule|f}}\n* Galician: {{t+|gl|amorodo|m}}, {{t+|gl|amorogo|m}}, {{t+|gl|morango|m}}, {{t+|gl|morote|m}}\n* Georgian: {{t|ka|მარწყვი}} {{q|cultivated}}, {{t|ka|ხენდრო}} {{q|wild}}\n* German: {{t+|de|Erdbeere|f}}\n*: Central Franconian: {{t|gmw-cfr|Erbel|f}}\n*: East Central German: {{t|gmw-ecg|Arbeer|f}}\n* Greek: {{t+|el|φράουλα|f}}, {{t+|el|χαμοκέρασο|n}}\n* Greenlandic: {{t|kl|jordbæri}}\n* Gujarati: {{t|gu|સ્ટ્રોબેરી|f}}\n* Haitian Creole: {{t|ht|frèz}}\n* Halkomelem: {{t|hur|schí:ya}}\n* Hawaiian: {{t|haw|ʻōhelo papa}}\n* Hebrew: {{t+|he|תּוּת שָׂדֶה|m|tr=tuth sađéh}}\n* Hindi: {{t|hi|स्ट्रॉबेरी}}, {{t|hi|हिसाल}}\n* Hungarian: {{t+|hu|eper}}, {{t+|hu|földi eper}}, {{t+|hu|szamóca}}\n* Hunsrik: {{t|hrx|Äerdbeer|f}}\n* Icelandic: {{t+|is|jarðarber|n}}\n* Ido: {{t+|io|frago}}\n* Indonesian: {{t+|id|arbei}}, {{t+|id|buah arbei}}, {{t+|id|stroberi}}\n* Inuktitut:\n*: Inuttitut: {{t|iu|akpiujak}}\n* Irish: {{t|ga|sú talún|f}}\n* Italian: {{t+|it|fragola|f}}\n* Japanese: {{t+|ja|イチゴ|tr=ichigo}}, {{t+|ja|苺|tr=いちご, ichigo}}, {{t+|ja|ストロベリー|tr=sutoroberī}}\n* Kaitag: {{t|xdq|ла́зе}}\n* Kannada: {{t|kn|ಸ್ಟ್ರಾಬೆರಿ}}\n* Karelian: {{t|krl|manšikka}}\n* Kazakh: {{t|kk|құлпынай}}, {{t+|kk|бүлдірген}}, {{t|kk|қойбүлдірген}}\n* Khmer: {{t|km|ហ្វ្រ៊ែហ្ស៍|tr=hvrêhs}}, {{t|km|ស្ត្របឺរី|tr=strâbœri}}\n* Korean: {{t+|ko|딸기}}\n*: Middle Korean: {{t|okm|ᄠᅡᆯ〮기〮}}\n* Kurdish:\n*: Northern Kurdish: {{t+|kmr|tûfiringî}}, {{t+|kmr|tûerd}}\n* Kyrgyz: {{t+|ky|кулпунай}}\n* Ladino: {{t|lad|freza}}, {{t|lad|frangula}}\n* Lao: {{t|lo|ໝາກສະຕໍເບີຣີ}}\n* Latgalian: {{t|ltg|zemneica|f}}\n* Latin: {{t|la|frāgum|n}}\n* Latvian: {{t+|lv|zemene|f}}\n* Lithuanian: {{t|lt|žemuogė|f}} {{q|any Fragaria}}, {{t+|lt|braškė|f}} {{q|Fragaria × ananassa}}\n* Livonian: {{t|liv|mõtsāmōškõz}} {{q|wild}}, {{t|liv|mōškõz}} {{q|cultivated}}\